Jadi dari jauh pun korang boleh start and off engine kereta korang. Memang padu lah. Jadi kalau korang nak buat, orang-orang Puchong tu dah dekat dah, korang boleh pergi. DMP Car Design, Papa Roger.

Kat sini, there are a lot of menus that you can choose from. Kat sini, you can get a food just as low as RM9.99 and with RM20, you can get a full set of food.  dan juga air. Jadi pada hari itu saya mencuba ayam kicap sambal kece dan ia sangat sedap dan bersama dengan ayam baltemil yang telah dicincang, ia sangat krisp dan keras dengan rasa. Dan selain daripada nasi, saya dapat mencuba keju manis yang sangat krim dan juga polok mis daging spageti ini. Dan saya dapat mengatakan bahawa ia tidak mahal sama sekali, sangat murah.  Sangat berguna. Rasa-rasa semuanya sangat lembut dan rumah. Dan saya yakinkan anda bahawa ini adalah penjualan bajet yang anda dapat. Dengan semua makanan, saya juga mencuba minuman mereka, yaitu lemonade ais, susu coklat, teh susu ais, dan juga kopi Saigon. Dan ia adalah tempat yang sangat bagus untuk anda periksa. Itu sahaja daripada saya. Terima kasih.

video_summary: The speaker discusses the effectiveness of robot trading in forex, stating that many people believe it can lead to consistent success, but in reality, it often fails to deliver as expected. The issue lies in the fact that robots are programmed to function in a specific way, but the market is constantly changing, making it difficult for them to adapt. The speaker also mentions that robots are often programmed based on past data, which may not be effective in the future. Additionally, robot trading is designed for short-term gains, making it prone to stop losses and triggering losses when market conditions change. The speaker advises against relying on robot trading as a shortcut to success in trading, instead encouraging viewers to think more critically about their approach.

Ada banyak sifu yang jual EA ataupun robot trading. Sebenarnya realitinya ialah, robot trading takkan berfungsi seperti yang korang harapkan. Dan oleh sebab market sentiasa berubah, in the future dia mungkin tidak begitu efektif. Yang korang kena faham ialah,  Robot trading ni sebenarnya diprogram untuk membuat keuntungan jangka masa pendek. Oleh sebab itu, bila keadaan market berubah, ia akan menyebabkan lebih mudah untuk stop loss, kena trigger dan korang akan mengalami kerugian berturut-turut. Jadi kalau korang fikir robot trading ni adalah jalan pintas untuk korang jadi suksesful dalam trading, please think again. Follow for more Forex videos.

video_summary: The speaker is discussing their video content, expressing mixed emotions as they announce the conclusion of their "Beginner 101" series and the upcoming launch of "Intermediate 101". They mention that the Beginner 101 series, which covered topics such as opening an account, starting to trade, and downloading necessary tools, is now available as a playlist on their TikTok profile. The speaker expresses their hope that their students will succeed in trading and make extra money, whether full-time or part-time. They also tease the Intermediate 101 series, which will cover advanced topics such as analysis, support, resistance, supply and demand, chart patterns, and market structure, all of which will be taught for free.

The speaker expresses their hope that their students will succeed in trading and make extra money, whether full-time or part-time. They also tease the Intermediate 101 series, which will cover advanced topics such as analysis, support, resistance, supply and demand, chart patterns, and market structure, all of which will be taught for free. video_summary: The speaker discusses their experience with using signals for trading, initially using Telegram but now relying on Artificial Intelligence (AI) for real-time data analysis and automated trading signals. The AI combines data with indicators to provide the best entry positions and can auto-trade signals on an exchange. This shift has made trading easier and less time-consuming, eliminating the need for manual checks and allowing for more flexibility. The AI also offers auto risk management and asset management, and the speaker invites interested viewers to learn more about using AI through weekly classes, with links provided in the bio.

transcription: Pernah guna signal dekat telegram? Pernah, pernah. Tapi tu dulu lah. Sekarang saya pakai AI lah. AI yang bagi signal. Dari AI? Okay. Tapi apa beza dah? Dia sebab AI baca real-time data. Combine dengan indikator untuk bagi best entry position. And one of the biggest reason AI yang saya guna ni boleh auto-trade signal yang diberi oleh AI tu dekat exchanger. Wuih, boleh auto-trade lah.  Haha betul. Disebab dulu kita tergeja-geja buka telegram untuk tengok signal sebab takut terlepas. Nak check tp lagi. Semua benda tu manual lah. Bila sibuk hal kerja dengan family jadi susah sikit nak trade tu. So that's why sekarang tu lebih tenang lah. Lebih mudah sebab AI bagi signal setiap masa. Jadi kita boleh pilih signal yang diberi oleh AI tu untuk di auto-trade kan dekat exchanger. video_summary: The speaker in the video explains how to open a trading account, specifically with GMI Markets Broker. There, users must fill in their details, including name, phone number, and email, which must match their identification. After logging in, users need to verify their account by uploading a photo of their ID, which will confirm their identity and enable trading. The speaker emphasizes that opening a trading account is easy and encourages viewers to share and like the video for future reference.

Lepas tu, dekat bawah tu kau akan nampak satu link. Kau tekan link tu, dia akan keluar beberapa option. Ada option Open Your Trading Account. Tekan Open Your Trading Account, kau akan redirect kepada satu website iaitu GMI Markets Broker yang aku recommend. Kemudian kau kena masukkan detail.  Nama kena sama dengan IC engkau, nombor phone yang boleh dihubungi, email yang boleh dapat terima email dan reply email. Bila kau dah isi semua email, kau dah isi semua detail engkau, engkau akan diloginkan dalam satu website iaitu website broker tu lah. Lepas kau dah login dalam website broker, benda seterusnya yang kau kena buat adalah verify your trading account.  Macam mana cara nak verify? Ambil gambar IC depan belakang, upload dalam website tu kemudian dia akan verify korang punya account dan dia dah sahkan yang kau ni adalah manusia yang wujud dan kau ni nak trading. So, semudah tu je nak buka trading account ni. Tak susah pun. Kalau kau rasa video ni bermanfaat, jangan lupa share, jangan lupa like, save video ni untuk kau tengokin future kalau-kalau terlepas. video_summary: The video explains how to profit from Forex, or Foreign Exchange, in a simple manner. The narrator uses an example of exchanging Malaysian Ringgit (RM) for US Dollars (USD) for travel to the US. Initially, RM4.80 is equivalent to USD1, and exchanging RM4,800 yields $1,000. Upon returning to Malaysia, the exchange rate has changed, with USD1 now equivalent to RM5. Exchanging $1,000 back to RM yields RM5,000, resulting in a profit of RM200. This illustrates how Forex works, with the narrator emphasizing it's a simple example, and encouraging viewers to understand the concept to potentially profit from it.

video_summary: The speaker advises against trading on 1-minute or 5-minute charts in Forex, referring to traders who do so as scalpers, and notes that many influencers on TikTok promote this method to earn high commissions from brokers. Scalping involves trading large lot sizes to achieve small profits, making traders more susceptible to market manipulation. The speaker cites an interview with a former trader from Singapore who worked at a large institution and states that research shows it's challenging to profitably trade in small time frames, recommending instead trading in at least 1-hour or 4-hour time frames where prices are more stable and less prone to manipulation.

video_summary: The speaker in the video responds to a comment from Abang Fizz, addressing his concerns about not withdrawing from trades and using various techniques and indicators. However, he realizes that he lacked a deep understanding of market structure, price action, and basic chart reading. The speaker stresses the importance of backtesting, practicing, and forward testing techniques, and encourages Abang Fizz to focus on a few techniques that work for him rather than trying to master many. He also advises against trading with techniques that one does not fully understand, as it can lead to emotional instability. The speaker concludes by urging Abang Fizz to revisit the basics and practice consistently, assuring him that he is not stupid, but rather needs to refine his approach.

video_summary: The video discusses the top three indicators for traders to use for free, specifically highlighting the Trendline with Breakout by Luxalgo, which can be applied to all currency pairs. This indicator automatically detects trendline breakouts and provides entry points for traders. To use it, traders need to open the 3D View, go to the Indicator section, and type in "Trail Line with Breakout" from Luxalgo. The indicator will then identify the breakout area and provide a signal for entry, allowing traders to potentially make a profit.

Nan was warned by his friend to be careful while riding through a particular stretch of road due to its notorious reputation for accidents and supernatural occurrences. Despite his initial bravado, Nan began to feel uneasy and his motorcycle suddenly stopped working at a deserted spot. He tried to call his friend, who advised him to recite Islamic prayers, which eventually allowed him to push the motorcycle but not start the engine. After his friend arrived and recited more prayers, the motorcycle was able to start again. Nan's friend revealed that the spot where they were stranded was infamous for accidents and supernatural occurrences, and Nan realized that he had underestimated the power of the unknown. video_summary: A group of Mat Rempit, Malaysian motorcycle enthusiasts, fled from the police and unexpectedly stopped at a Islamic lecture by Ustaz Azhar Idrus. The Ustaz explained that their actions of attending the lecture would be rewarded, as they had shown an interest in learning about their faith. However, their initial act of fleeing from the police would not be rewarded. The Ustaz emphasized that it's the intention and actions that matter, not one's appearance, and encouraged the youth to seek knowledge and attend Islamic lectures without fear of judgment, as long as they cover their aurat, or private parts, and show respect.

combined_text: The Road Transport Department (JPJ) of Pahang, Malaysia, conducted a road safety advocacy program at Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Mat Kilau, aimed at promoting road safety awareness among students, particularly those who use motorcycles to commute. The program included motorcycle inspections and a lecture on road safety, emphasizing the importance of wearing helmets and adhering to traffic laws. The JPJ officials also highlighted common mistakes made by motorcyclists, such as not displaying number plates and not wearing helmets, and encouraged students to take responsibility for their safety on the road.
